The paper is motivated by applications in telecommunications, specifically in modeling Internet traffic, which suggests that it belongs to the cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) sub-category. The paper also deals with statistical modeling, which could place it in the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category. The method described is computationally and analytically simple, which could make it relevant to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category. The paper also deals with generating time series, which could place it in the cs.MA (Machine Learning) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with statistical phenomena, which could make it relevant to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category.
